labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.actioncomponent","layer_id":"ux","type":"actioncomponent","title":"ActionComponent","description":"Interactive element that triggers actions (button, menu, link, voice command)","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":8}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.actionpattern","layer_id":"ux","type":"actionpattern","title":"ActionPattern","description":"Reusable action configuration for common user interactions. Defines the trigger, feedback mechanism, and optional target for recurring UX patterns. Example: 'confirm-and-delete' pattern — trigger: click on delete button, feedback: confirmation modal then success toast, targetRef: the item being deleted.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.chartseries","layer_id":"ux","type":"chartseries","title":"ChartSeries","description":"Configuration for a data series within a chart component, specifying data source, visualization type, colors, and legend properties. Defines how data is visualized in charts.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":6}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.componentreference","layer_id":"ux","type":"componentreference","title":"ComponentReference","description":"A declarative placeholder in a parent component's named slot, pointing to another component to be rendered there. Unlike ComponentInstance (a concrete rendered occurrence), ComponentReference is a composition declaration that says 'render this component in this slot of the parent', analogous to the HTML slot element.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.dataconfig","layer_id":"ux","type":"dataconfig","title":"DataConfig","description":"Configuration for data binding and state management within UI components, defining data sources, transformation pipelines, and update triggers. Manages component data flow.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.errorconfig","layer_id":"ux","type":"errorconfig","title":"ErrorConfig","description":"Configuration for error handling and display within UI components, specifying error message formats, retry behavior, fallback content, and user guidance. Ensures consistent error UX.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.experiencestate","layer_id":"ux","type":"experiencestate","title":"ExperienceState","description":"Distinct state that the experience can be in (works across all channels)","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":9}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.layoutconfig","layer_id":"ux","type":"layoutconfig","title":"LayoutConfig","description":"Configuration for UI layout structure, defining grid systems, responsive breakpoints, spacing rules, and component arrangement patterns. Controls visual organization of the interface.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":16}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.librarycomponent","layer_id":"ux","type":"librarycomponent","title":"LibraryComponent","description":"Reusable UI component definition that can be instantiated in multiple UXSpecs","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":8}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.librarysubview","layer_id":"ux","type":"librarysubview","title":"LibrarySubView","description":"Reusable, non-routable grouping of components intended to be composed into Views or other SubViews. Unlike View, LibrarySubView has no route and cannot be navigated to directly. It exists purely as a reusable composition unit, analogous to an HTML template element.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.stateaction","layer_id":"ux","type":"stateaction","title":"StateAction","description":"A concrete action bound to a specific ExperienceState lifecycle event. Instances are bound to a state and lifecycle hook; for reusable parameterizable definitions use StateActionTemplate. Examples: scroll-to-top (lifecycle: on-enter), focus-first-field (lifecycle: on-enter), dispatch-analytics-event (lifecycle: on-exit).","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.stateactiontemplate","layer_id":"ux","type":"stateactiontemplate","title":"StateActionTemplate","description":"A parameterizable, reusable definition of an action to execute during state transitions. StateActionTemplate is the definition; StateAction is the concrete usage bound to a specific ExperienceState and lifecycle hook. Example: a 'scroll-to-top' template with a 'targetId' parameter, instantiated as a StateAction on multiple states.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.statepattern","layer_id":"ux","type":"statepattern","title":"StatePattern","description":"Reusable state machine template for common UX interaction flows, composed of named ExperienceStates and transitions. Canonical examples: 'wizard' — multi-step form with back/next/submit transitions; 'optimistic-update' — loading → success/error with retry; 'tab-panel' — N peer states with tab-driven transitions; 'authenticated-route' — unauthenticated → redirect/login → authenticated.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.statetransition","layer_id":"ux","type":"statetransition","title":"StateTransition","description":"A directed edge in the ExperienceState machine, owned by its source ExperienceState. Specifies the trigger event, destination state, optional guard condition, and side-effect actions. The 'from' state is implicitly the ExperienceState that contains this transition via relationship.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.subview","layer_id":"ux","type":"subview","title":"SubView","description":"A non-routable UI fragment embedded within a parent View. Two usage modes: (1) Library instance — 'ref' is populated with a ux.librarysubview specNodeId, rendering that reusable fragment; (2) Inline definition — 'ref' is absent and the SubView defines its own composition inline. SubViews are not independently routable; use View for routable pages.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.tablecolumn","layer_id":"ux","type":"tablecolumn","title":"TableColumn","description":"Configuration for a single column within a data table component, specifying header, data binding, sorting, filtering, and rendering options. Defines table structure and behavior.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":9}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.transitiontemplate","layer_id":"ux","type":"transitiontemplate","title":"TransitionTemplate","description":"Defines reusable animation and transition patterns for state changes, page navigation, or component lifecycle events. Ensures consistent motion design across the application.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":6}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.uxapplication","layer_id":"ux","type":"uxapplication","title":"UXApplication","description":"Application-level UX configuration that groups UXSpecs and defines shared settings","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":7}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.uxlibrary","layer_id":"ux","type":"uxlibrary","title":"UXLibrary","description":"Collection of reusable UI components and sub-views that can be shared across applications","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":9}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_ux
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"ux.uxspec","layer_id":"ux","type":"uxspec","title":"UXSpec","description":"Complete UX specification for a single experience (visual, voice, chat, SMS)","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":7}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.contextvariation","layer_id":"testing","type":"contextvariation","title":"ContextVariation","description":"A distinct test type or environmental context under which a coverage target may be invoked, used to parameterize test design across different execution conditions (functional correctness, load behavior, security posture, regression state). Maps to environmental needs documented in IEEE 829-2008 test design specifications.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.coverageexclusion","layer_id":"testing","type":"coverageexclusion","title":"CoverageExclusion","description":"A formally approved exclusion of a coverage target or requirement from the test coverage model, documenting the rationale, accepted risk, and accountable approver per test plan scope documentation in IEEE 829-2008.","required_attribute_count":3,"total_attribute_count":6}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.coveragegap","layer_id":"testing","type":"coveragegap","title":"CoverageGap","description":"An identified deficit between required and achieved test coverage for a target or requirement, typically surfaced during test summary reporting per IEEE 829-2008. Gaps require remediation, risk acceptance (CoverageExclusion), or deferral.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.coveragerequirement","layer_id":"testing","type":"coveragerequirement","title":"CoverageRequirement","description":"A specification of coverage criteria that must be satisfied for a TestCoverageTarget, defining which input partitions, context variations, and outcome categories must be exercised, per test design specification requirements in IEEE 829-2008.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.coveragesummary","layer_id":"testing","type":"coveragesummary","title":"CoverageSummary","description":"Aggregated coverage status across all targets and requirements within a test coverage model, suitable for test summary reporting.","required_attribute_count":3,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.environmentfactor","layer_id":"testing","type":"environmentfactor","title":"EnvironmentFactor","description":"A specific environmental variable (OS version, network latency, locale setting, hardware configuration, dependency version) documented as affecting test behavior. Used to parameterize ContextVariation instances with concrete environmental constraints per IEEE 829-2008 environmental needs specification.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.inputpartitionselection","layer_id":"testing","type":"inputpartitionselection","title":"InputPartitionSelection","description":"A specification of which values from an InputSpacePartition must be exercised within a CoverageRequirement, supporting selective coverage of equivalence classes per IEEE 829-2008 test design specification. When coverAllCategories is true, all partition values are included except those in excludeValues; otherwise, only the values listed in coverValues are included.","required_attribute_count":4,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.inputselection","layer_id":"testing","type":"inputselection","title":"InputSelection","description":"A concrete input value assignment for a TestCaseSketch, binding an abstract partition representative value (selectedValue) to a specific concrete test datum (concreteValue), per test case input specification in IEEE 829-2008.","required_attribute_count":4,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.inputspacepartition","layer_id":"testing","type":"inputspacepartition","title":"InputSpacePartition","description":"Partitioning of an input dimension into testable equivalence classes, where each entry in the partitions array represents a PartitionValue (an equivalence class with a label, category, and representative value), enabling structured coverage analysis per IEEE 829-2008 equivalence partitioning guidance.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.outcomecategory","layer_id":"testing","type":"outcomecategory","title":"OutcomeCategory","description":"An abstract category of observable outcomes (e.g., success, validation error, authorization error, timeout) associated with a TestCoverageTarget, used during test design to organize expected results before test case specification per IEEE 829-2008. Distinguished from specific assertions — OutcomeCategory defines the class of outcome, not the exact expected value.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":2}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.partitiondependency","layer_id":"testing","type":"partitiondependency","title":"PartitionDependency","description":"A constraint specifying how selection of a partition value in one field affects valid or available partition values in another field, enabling combinatorial test design to avoid invalid input combinations per IEEE 829-2008 test design specification.","required_attribute_count":4,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.partitionvalue","layer_id":"testing","type":"partitionvalue","title":"PartitionValue","description":"An individual equivalence class within an InputSpacePartition, characterized by a label, representative value, and optional constraint expression, used to enumerate the testable categories of an input dimension per IEEE 829-2008 test design specification.","required_attribute_count":5,"total_attribute_count":6}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.targetcoveragesummary","layer_id":"testing","type":"targetcoveragesummary","title":"TargetCoverageSummary","description":"Coverage metrics summary for a single test coverage target","required_attribute_count":4,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.targetinputfield","layer_id":"testing","type":"targetinputfield","title":"TargetInputField","description":"An association between a TestCoverageTarget and a specific input field of the target artifact, defining which InputSpacePartition applies to that field and documenting its coverage relevance per IEEE 829-2008 test case specification.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.testcasesketch","layer_id":"testing","type":"testcasesketch","title":"TestCaseSketch","description":"A design-time test case specification that selects concrete input partition values for a CoverageRequirement, serving as the bridge between test design (InputPartitionSelection) and executable test case specification per IEEE 829-2008. Exists in sketch (unimplemented) or implemented status — not yet tied to a specific test runner or execution framework.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.testcoveragemodel","layer_id":"testing","type":"testcoveragemodel","title":"TestCoverageModel","description":"The root artifact of a testing layer coverage specification, aggregating all TestCoverageTargets, InputSpacePartitions, ContextVariations, CoverageRequirements, and TestCaseSketches for an application. Corresponds to the test plan document structure in IEEE 829-2008, providing a single point of reference for coverage governance.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_testing
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"testing.testcoveragetarget","layer_id":"testing","type":"testcoveragetarget","title":"TestCoverageTarget","description":"An artifact or functionality that requires test coverage","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.artifact","layer_id":"technology","type":"artifact","title":"Artifact","description":"A piece of data that is used or produced in a software development process, or by the deployment and operation of an IT system, such as a source file, executable, script, or configuration file.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.communicationnetwork","layer_id":"technology","type":"communicationnetwork","title":"CommunicationNetwork","description":"A set of structures that connects nodes for the purpose of transmission, routing, and reception of data, such as a LAN, WAN, or VPN.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.device","layer_id":"technology","type":"device","title":"Device","description":"A physical IT resource upon which system software and artifacts may be stored or deployed for execution, such as a server, workstation, mobile device, or IoT sensor.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.node","layer_id":"technology","type":"node","title":"Node","description":"A computational or physical resource that hosts, manipulates, or interacts with other computational or physical resources, such as a server cluster, virtual machine host, or container runtime.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.path","layer_id":"technology","type":"path","title":"Path","description":"A link between two or more nodes through which those nodes can exchange data, representing a logical communication channel such as a network route, API connection, or message channel.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.systemsoftware","layer_id":"technology","type":"systemsoftware","title":"SystemSoftware","description":"Software that provides or contributes to an environment for storing, executing, and using other software or data deployed within it, such as an operating system, container runtime, database engine, or middleware platform.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.technologycollaboration","layer_id":"technology","type":"technologycollaboration","title":"TechnologyCollaboration","description":"An aggregate of two or more technology active structure elements that work together to perform collective technology behavior, such as a cluster of servers, a distributed cache, or a microservice mesh.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.technologyevent","layer_id":"technology","type":"technologyevent","title":"TechnologyEvent","description":"A technology behavior element that denotes a state change in the technology layer that triggers or results from technology behavior, such as a system alert, infrastructure notification, scheduled job trigger, or deployment completion signal.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.technologyfunction","layer_id":"technology","type":"technologyfunction","title":"TechnologyFunction","description":"A collection of technology behavior that can be performed by a node, representing an internal automated capability such as data replication, load balancing, or log rotation.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.technologyinteraction","layer_id":"technology","type":"technologyinteraction","title":"TechnologyInteraction","description":"A unit of collective technology behavior performed by two or more collaborating nodes, such as a distributed transaction, inter-service handshake, or cluster failover protocol.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.technologyinterface","layer_id":"technology","type":"technologyinterface","title":"TechnologyInterface","description":"Point of access where technology services are available","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_technology
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"technology.technologyprocess","layer_id":"technology","type":"technologyprocess","title":"TechnologyProcess","description":"A sequence of technology behaviors that achieves a specific technology result, such as a deployment pipeline, backup job, certificate renewal workflow, or container orchestration sequence.","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.accesscondition","layer_id":"security","type":"accesscondition","title":"AccessCondition","description":"Defines a single boolean predicate evaluated against a request context attribute (field), comparing the runtime value using a specified operator. Composed inside a PolicyRule condition chain to form compound access control expressions.","required_attribute_count":5,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.accountabilityrequirement","layer_id":"security","type":"accountabilityrequirement","title":"AccountabilityRequirement","description":"Expresses who is obligated to provide evidence that a specific action occurred and under what conditions that evidence can be challenged. Distinct from AuditConfig, which defines what events are captured — this node defines the obligation to prove an action took place. Implements NIST SP 800-53 AU-10 non-repudiation.","required_attribute_count":5,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.actor","layer_id":"security","type":"actor","title":"Actor","description":"A named principal — human user, service account, automated system, or external entity — whose identity and trust level govern what operations it may perform. Associates with Roles for permission grouping and with SeparationOfDuty and Delegation controls, per NIST SP 800-53 AC-2 (Account Management) and SP 800-207 (Zero Trust Architecture).","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.auditconfig","layer_id":"security","type":"auditconfig","title":"AuditConfig","description":"Configuration for security audit logging, specifying what events to capture, retention periods, storage destinations, and compliance requirements. Enables security monitoring and forensic analysis.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":6}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.authenticationconfig","layer_id":"security","type":"authenticationconfig","title":"AuthenticationConfig","description":"Specifies how principals are verified before accessing protected resources, including the identity provider, multi-factor requirements, session lifetime, and credential policy references. Scoped per application or service. Maps to NIST SP 800-53 IA-2, IA-5, and IA-11.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":6}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.bindingofduty","layer_id":"security","type":"bindingofduty","title":"BindingOfDuty","description":"Obligation control requiring that a single actor who initiates a task must also complete it, preventing task hijacking or inconsistent workflow state that could be exploited by a different actor. Complements SeparationOfDuty by enforcing task continuity rather than task segregation. Anchored to NIST SP 800-53 CM-5 (Access Restrictions for Change) and workflow integrity controls.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.condition","layer_id":"security","type":"condition","title":"Condition","description":"A reusable logical expression evaluated against request context (time, location, user attributes, resource state) to determine when a SecurityPolicy rule applies. Distinct from AccessCondition, which is a concrete field+operator+value predicate composed inside a PolicyRule condition chain.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.countermeasure","layer_id":"security","type":"countermeasure","title":"Countermeasure","description":"A security control or mitigation technique that reduces the likelihood or impact of a specific threat. Maps to NIST SP 800-53 controls by type (technical, operational, management) and tracks implementation status and residual risk.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.delegation","layer_id":"security","type":"delegation","title":"Delegation","description":"Explicit transfer of permissions or authority from a delegator to a delegatee, subject to scope constraints and optional time bounds. Supports least-privilege enforcement (NIST AC-6) by enabling time-limited privilege elevation rather than permanent role assignment.","required_attribute_count":3,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.evidence","layer_id":"security","type":"evidence","title":"Evidence","description":"An artifact that provides verifiable proof of an action or event for non-repudiation and audit purposes. Anchored to NIST SP 800-53 AU-10 (Non-repudiation), evidence types range from cryptographic signatures to plain audit log entries, with strength characterizing the assurance level per NIST SP 800-63-3.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.fieldaccesscontrol","layer_id":"security","type":"fieldaccesscontrol","title":"FieldAccessControl","description":"Defines access restrictions and transformation rules for a specific data field, controlling how sensitive values are masked or redacted when exposed to unauthorized principals. Used within SecureResource fieldAccess to enforce field-level data protection per NIST SP 800-53 AC-3 and SC-28.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.informationentity","layer_id":"security","type":"informationentity","title":"InformationEntity","description":"Named information asset subject to fine-grained access rights and data classification. Represents a logical grouping of data (e.g., customer PII, financial records) whose access is governed by associated InformationRight grants and AccountabilityRequirements, per NIST SP 800-53 AC-3 and IP-1.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.informationright","layer_id":"security","type":"informationright","title":"InformationRight","description":"A granular access grant specifying which operations a named actor may perform on an InformationEntity, subject to a qualifying constraint expression. Implements attribute-based access control (ABAC) at the information asset level, per NIST SP 800-162 (ABAC Guide) and NIST SP 800-53 AC-3(14).","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.needtoknow","layer_id":"security","type":"needtoknow","title":"NeedToKnow","description":"Restricts access to a resource to only those actors whose stated purpose requires it, implementing the NIST SP 800-53 AC-3(3) mandatory access control principle. JustificationRequired enforces that actors must declare their purpose before access is granted.","required_attribute_count":4,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.passwordpolicy","layer_id":"security","type":"passwordpolicy","title":"PasswordPolicy","description":"Defines password complexity, rotation, and lockout requirements for credential-based authentication. Implements NIST SP 800-53 IA-5(1) controls including minimum length, character class requirements, history enforcement, and brute-force lockout thresholds.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":10}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.permission","layer_id":"security","type":"permission","title":"Permission","description":"An atomic grant authorizing a specific action (e.g., read, write, execute) on a resource within a defined scope. Permissions are assigned to Roles and enforced by SecureResource access control lists. Implements NIST SP 800-53 AC-3 access enforcement and AC-6 least privilege.","required_attribute_count":3,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.policyaction","layer_id":"security","type":"policyaction","title":"PolicyAction","description":"The enforcement action executed when a SecurityPolicy rule condition is met. Defines the system response to a policy match (allow, deny, remediation, notification), ensuring consistent policy enforcement across the security model per NIST SP 800-53 CA-9 (Internal System Connections) and SI-3 (Malicious Code Protection).","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.policyrule","layer_id":"security","type":"policyrule","title":"PolicyRule","description":"An atomic policy evaluation unit consisting of a condition predicate and an enforcement effect (PERMIT or DENY), with optional obligation actions executed upon match. Multiple PolicyRules compose a SecurityPolicy evaluated in priority order.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.resourceoperation","layer_id":"security","type":"resourceoperation","title":"ResourceOperation","description":"A permitted operation that an actor may perform on a secured resource, forming the verb component of a subject-verb-object access control policy. Bound to AccessConditions, RateLimits, and AuditConfig nodes via the security policy model, per NIST SP 800-53 AC-3 (Access Enforcement).","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":5}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.retentionpolicy","layer_id":"security","type":"retentionpolicy","title":"RetentionPolicy","description":"Defines how long security-related data (audit logs, access records, encryption keys) must be retained, archival strategies, and secure deletion procedures. Ensures compliance with regulatory requirements.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.role","layer_id":"security","type":"role","title":"Role","description":"A named collection of Permissions implementing RBAC per NIST SP 800-53 AC-2 and AC-6. Roles can inherit from parent roles (role hierarchy), accumulating permissions transitively. The level attribute defines the role privilege tier for least-privilege enforcement.","required_attribute_count":3,"total_attribute_count":4}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.secureresource","layer_id":"security","type":"secureresource","title":"SecureResource","description":"Represents a named resource subject to security controls, defining the operations that can be performed on it and optional field-level access restrictions. Acts as the resource component in subject-action-resource access control triples per NIST SP 800-53 AC-3.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"security.securitymodel","layer_id":"security","type":"securitymodel","title":"SecurityModel","description":"The root aggregate for an application's security posture, composing authentication, authorization (roles, permissions, resources), threat model, data classification, accountability requirements, and policies into a unified security specification. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_security

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_navigation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_navigation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_navigation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_navigation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_navigation
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"navigation.navigationflow","layer_id":"navigation","type":"navigationflow","title":"NavigationFlow","description":"Sequence of routes that realizes a business process","required_attribute_count":0,"total_attribute_count":2}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_navigation
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"navigation.navigationgraph","layer_id":"navigation","type":"navigationgraph","title":"NavigationGraph","description":"Root container for an application's complete routing structure, composing all Route, NavigationTransition, and NavigationGuard nodes into a unified navigation model.","required_attribute_count":2,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_navigation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_motivation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_motivation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_motivation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_motivation
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"motivation.stakeholder","layer_id":"motivation","type":"stakeholder","title":"Stakeholder","description":"Individual, team, or organization that has an interest in, or is affected by, the effects of the architecture.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":2}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_motivation

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_store

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_store

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_store

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_store
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"data-store.namespace","layer_id":"data-store","type":"namespace","title":"Namespace","description":"A logical grouping of database objects within a database instance. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_store
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"data-store.retentionpolicy","layer_id":"data-store","type":"retentionpolicy","title":"RetentionPolicy","description":"A data lifecycle management policy that governs how long data is retained and what action is taken when the retention period expires. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_store
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"data-store.storedlogic","layer_id":"data-store","type":"storedlogic","title":"StoredLogic","description":"Stored computation logic that executes within the data store engine. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_store

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_data_model

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_business

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_business

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_application

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_application

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_application

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_application
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"application.applicationinteraction","layer_id":"application","type":"applicationinteraction","title":"ApplicationInteraction","description":"Collective application behavior performed by two or more application components working in collaboration, representing their joint behavioral contribution.","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":2}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_application
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"application.applicationinterface","layer_id":"application","type":"applicationinterface","title":"ApplicationInterface","description":"Point of access where application service is available","required_attribute_count":1,"total_attribute_count":3}

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_apm

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_apm

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"api.parameter","layer_id":"api","type":"parameter","title":"Parameter","description":"Defines an input to an API operation by location, name, and schema. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"api.pathitem","layer_id":"api","type":"pathitem","title":"PathItem","description":"Groups all HTTP operations available under a single URL path pattern (e.g., /users/{userId}). labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"api.response","layer_id":"api","type":"response","title":"Response","description":"Defines a single HTTP response returned by an operation, including its description, body content (keyed by MIME type), response headers, and optional hypermedia links. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"api.responses","layer_id":"api","type":"responses","title":"Responses","description":"A map of HTTP status codes (e.g., 200, 404, default) to Response objects describing each possible outcome of an operation. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"api.schema","layer_id":"api","type":"schema","title":"Schema","description":"Inline data type definition using a subset of JSON Schema Draft 7, used within API operations to describe request/response data shapes. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"api.securityscheme","layer_id":"api","type":"securityscheme","title":"SecurityScheme","description":"Defines an authentication/authorization mechanism for the API. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api
properties:JSON: {"spec_node_id":"api.server","layer_id":"api","type":"server","title":"Server","description":"Defines a server URL (optionally templated with {variable} placeholders) where the API is deployed. labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api

labels:LABEL: SpecNode;SpecNode_api

TIME_SERIES: time-indexed measurements (InfluxDB, TimescaleDB). GRAPH: nodes and edges with traversal (Neo4j, Neptune). SEARCH_ENGINE: full-text search and analytics (Elasticsearch, OpenSearch). ALERT_RULE: threshold or anomaly alerting (time-series, monitoring). CUSTOM: engine-specific mechanism not listed."}
